Recommends: apt-transport-tor
Description: post-quantum anonymous overlay network
 MOOR is a Tor-style 3-hop onion-routing network with hybrid
 post-quantum cryptography on every link and circuit. Identity is
 Ed25519 + Falcon-512; key exchange is X25519 + ML-KEM-768; consensus
 is signed Ed25519 + ML-DSA-65.
 .
 The same binary is the client (SOCKS5 proxy), the relay, the
 directory authority, the bridge, and the hidden service. Mode is
 selected via /etc/moor/moor.conf or --mode on the command line.
 .
 This package installs the binary, manpage, a disabled-by-default
 systemd unit, and a /etc/moor skeleton. Edit moor.conf and run
 `systemctl enable --now moor` to activate.
